name: Headrests cores
description: Our headrests manufactured from Expanded Polypropylene can be combined with steel frames, fittings and comfort foams.

name: Plastic foam
description: Plastic foams like expanded polypropylene (EPP) and expanded polystyrene (EPS) are lightweight and flexible materials widely used throughout the automotive market for their outstanding shock-absorbing performance.

name: Car cockpit
description: Car cockpit parts like the EPP steering wheel column paddings and knee paddings are indispensable injury protection car elements in modern vehicles.

name: EPP car door pads
description: Car door pads constructed from Expanded Polypropylene are typically used for lateral impact absorbtion.

name: EPP trunk compartment
description: Expanded Polypropylene is the preferred material that our OEM and Tier 1 customers choose for in-boot tool and spare wheel accessory kits as well as battery covers and other car elements.

name: Baby car seats
description: The EPP foam exceptional insulating properties ensure thermal comfort during transport of the child safety seat outside of the vehicle, and the light weight of EPP child seats' components and bases reduces its weight, substantially improving convenience of use.
